790x5193+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F48%2F76b39df94984b37c009094450e1c%2Fap24264825320620.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7790x5193+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F48%2F76b39df94984b37c009094450e1c%2Fap24264825320620.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7790x5193+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F48%2F76b39df94984b37c009094450e1c%2Fap24264825320620.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7790x5193+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F48%2F76b39df94984b37c009094450e1c%2Fap24264825320620.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7790x5193+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F48%2F76b39df94984b37c009094450e1c%2Fap24264825320620.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7790x5193+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F48%2F76b39df94984b37c009094450e1c%2Fap24264825320620.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7790x5193+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F48%2F76b39df94984b37c009094450e1c%2Fap24264825320620.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7790x5193+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F48%2F76b39df94984b37c009094450e1c%2Fap24264825320620.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7790x5193+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F48%2F76b39df94984b37c009094450e1c%2Fap24264825320620.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7790x5193+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F18%2F48%2F76b39df94984b37c009094450e1c%2Fap24264825320620.jpg" class="img" alt="Pennsylvania Secretary of the Commonwealth Al Schmidt, participates in an election forum, Thursday, Sept. 19, in Ann Arbor, Mich. (AP Photo/Carlos Osorio)" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Pennsylvania Secretary of the Commonwealth Al Schmidt, participates in an election forum, Thursday, Sept. 19, in Ann Arbor, Mich.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Carlos Osorio/AP/AP                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;NPR is visiting &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/series/1241382501/we-the-voters"&gt;&lt;em&gt;six key swing states&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; that will likely decide this year’s historic election. This week, Morning Edition is in Pennsylvania to listen to voters about what matters to them and how that will affect their vote.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It is unlikely we'll know who won the battleground state of Pennsylvania on Election night. &lt;/strong&gt;That's because a law created four years ago doesn't allow election officials to open mail-in ballots until the morning of Nov. 5. Lehigh County Executive Phil Armstrong says the county will have thousands of ballots to go through, and the longer it takes, the more people will think something has gone wrong. Pennsylvania’s Secretary of the Commonwealth Al Schmidt, who oversees the state's vote count, &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=nx-s1-5157599:x"&gt;breaks down the process&lt;/a&gt; on &lt;em&gt;Morning Edition&lt;/em&gt; with host Michel Martin.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Picture show&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-26594" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4000;         --source-height: 2248;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4000x2248+0+414/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F0b%2Fa6%2F1e9b1867480593fd7d39cf1d5e72%2Fmalnutrition-nigeria-2.jpg" class="img" alt="Toyin feeds her 3-year-old daughter, Kudirat, while her husband, Saheed, tends to their other two children." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Toyin feeds her 3-year-old daughter, Kudirat, while her husband, Saheed, tends to their other two children.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Sope Adelaja for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“Severe child food poverty” is on the rise.&lt;/strong&gt; One in four children under the age of five worldwide is unable to access a nutritious diet, according to a UNICEF report. This amounts to 181 million young children. Rising food prices, climate crises, harmful food-marketing strategies, disruptions in food supply and other factors are contributing to the problem. In addition, low-income countries struggle to regulate aggressive advertising of processed snack foods, leading to many children consuming unhealthy, inexpensive options instead of nutrient-rich foods. &lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;📷 &lt;strong&gt;See photos&lt;/strong&gt; of &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/goats-and-soda/2024/09/25/g-s1-24488/photos-childhood-food-poverty-malnutrition"&gt;how nine families cope&lt;/a&gt; when they can't afford three healthy meals daily.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-29207" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 3672;         --source-height: 2066;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3672x2066+0+344/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F96%2F68%2Fd7429a03459ab7930f0adc30788a%2Fap24295503561532.jpg" class="img" alt="This image provided by the Houston Fire Department shows the scene of a helicopter crash in the city's Second Ward, Sunday, Oct. 20, 2024." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 This image provided by the Houston Fire Department shows the scene of a helicopter crash in the city's Second Ward, Sunday, Oct. 20, 2024.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          AP/Houston Fire Department                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Four people are dead, including a child, after&lt;/strong&gt; a helicopter &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/21/nx-s1-5159582/helicopter-crash-houston-radio-tower"&gt;crashed into a radio tower&lt;/a&gt; in Houston Sunday night, officials say.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The men known as the Central Park Five are suing&lt;/strong&gt; former President Donald Trump for &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/09/11/nx-s1-5108632/central-park-five-trump-debate"&gt;defamation over comments he made&lt;/a&gt; during last month's presidential debate, according to a lawsuit filed. The men were exonerated after being wrongfully convicted in 1989 of a brutal assault on a New York jogger.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Samantha Hodge-Williams had to undergo emergency surgery when doctors discovered an ovarian mass in 1996. &lt;/strong&gt;A singing aesthetician — and &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/21/nx-s1-5159740/anesthesiologist-surgery-good-news-kindness"&gt;unsung hero — helped ease her stress&lt;/a&gt; on the operating table, and has stayed in her thoughts through multiple surgeries later in her life.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
