ettyimages-1473989233.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3509x1974+0+370/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Ff4%2F99c25b7d43aa9e7b2c140df1e4b0%2Fgettyimages-1473989233.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3509x1974+0+370/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Ff4%2F99c25b7d43aa9e7b2c140df1e4b0%2Fgettyimages-1473989233.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3509x1974+0+370/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Ff4%2F99c25b7d43aa9e7b2c140df1e4b0%2Fgettyimages-1473989233.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3509x1974+0+370/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Ff4%2F99c25b7d43aa9e7b2c140df1e4b0%2Fgettyimages-1473989233.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3509x1974+0+370/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Ff4%2F99c25b7d43aa9e7b2c140df1e4b0%2Fgettyimages-1473989233.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3509x1974+0+370/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Ff4%2F99c25b7d43aa9e7b2c140df1e4b0%2Fgettyimages-1473989233.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/3509x1974+0+370/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F28%2Ff4%2F99c25b7d43aa9e7b2c140df1e4b0%2Fgettyimages-1473989233.jpg" class="img" alt="Liam Payne, seen here at the 2023 premiere of the film All of These Voices, a documentary about his One Direction band mate Louis Tomlinson." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Liam Payne, seen here at the 2023 premiere of the film &lt;em&gt;All of These Voices&lt;/em&gt;, a documentary about his One Direction band mate Louis Tomlinson.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Kate Green/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Liam Payne, who rose to fame as a singer in the boy band One Direction, died&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/16/nx-s1-5155192/liam-payne-one-direction-obituary"&gt;while in Buenos Aires&lt;/a&gt;, according to multiple news agencies. He was 31.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Over 11 million pounds of ready-to-eat meat and poultry has been recalled due to listeria concerns. &lt;/strong&gt;This includes salads, wraps, frozen meals and more &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/16/nx-s1-5154865/recall-listeria-meat-chicken-brucepac-list"&gt;sold at chains like Target, Trader Joe's and Walmart&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nebraska’s highest court ruled against top state officials,&lt;/strong&gt; upholding a law allowing felons to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/16/nx-s1-5155077/nebraska-felon-voting-ruling"&gt;register to vote after completing&lt;/a&gt; their sentences.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
