      <title>Harris courts Black male voters. And, worries that Israel is starving north Gaza</title>
      <author>Brittney Melton</author>
      <link>https://www.npr.org/2024/10/15/g-s1-28264/up-first-newsletter-vice-president-harris-black-male-voters-israel-northern-gaza-conflict</link>
      <comments>https://text.npr.org/2024/10/15/g-s1-28264/up-first-newsletter-vice-president-harris-black-male-voters-israel-northern-gaza-conflict</comments>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.npr.org/2024/10/15/g-s1-28264/up-first-newsletter-vice-president-harris-black-male-voters-israel-northern-gaza-conflict</guid>
      <pubDate>Tue, 15 Oct 2024 12:10:37 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;div id="storytext" class="storytext storylocation linkLocation"&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Good morning. You're reading the Up First newsletter. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/newsletter/news"&gt;Subscribe&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; here to get it delivered to your inbox, and &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/podcasts/510318/up-first/"&gt;listen&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; to the Up First podcast for all the news you need to start your day.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Today's top stories&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Today, Vice President Harris is set to announce initiatives aimed at winning over Black voters, particularly men. &lt;/strong&gt;She has pledged to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/13/nx-s1-5151968/harris-weed-crypto"&gt;legalize recreational marijuana&lt;/a&gt;, protect cryptocurrency assets and give 1 million fully forgivable loans of up to $20,000 for Black entrepreneurs and others to start businesses. Polls show that Black men are not as enthusiastic about Harris as they were about President Biden in 2020. Some are showing interest in former President Donald Trump. Democrats are worried that even a small shift in the Black male vote could harm Harris' chances of winning crucial swing states needed to secure the White House.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-28116" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4872;         --source-height: 2741;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4872x2741+0+273/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fae%2Fd7%2F5141507249aeba6bdf663d6aef32%2Fgettyimages-2177417560.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4872x2741+0+273/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fn