s-1.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fb0%2F97ffcc0146c4bf0829820b007f19%2Fcolombia-manacillos-1.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fb0%2F97ffcc0146c4bf0829820b007f19%2Fcolombia-manacillos-1.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fb0%2F97ffcc0146c4bf0829820b007f19%2Fcolombia-manacillos-1.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fb0%2F97ffcc0146c4bf0829820b007f19%2Fcolombia-manacillos-1.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fb0%2F97ffcc0146c4bf0829820b007f19%2Fcolombia-manacillos-1.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fb0%2F97ffcc0146c4bf0829820b007f19%2Fcolombia-manacillos-1.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fb0%2F97ffcc0146c4bf0829820b007f19%2Fcolombia-manacillos-1.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fb0%2F97ffcc0146c4bf0829820b007f19%2Fcolombia-manacillos-1.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/6000x3375+0+313/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F4c%2Fb0%2F97ffcc0146c4bf0829820b007f19%2Fcolombia-manacillos-1.jpg" class="img" alt="Camilo Garcia peeks through a curtain of his house on the morning of March 29, 2024, in the town of Juntas, Buenaventura, Colombia. The community gathers during Holy Week to celebrate the Manacillos festival, an ancestral ritual originating in the upper part of the Yurumangui River. Photographer: Nathalia Angarita" loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Camilo Garcia peeks through a curtain of his house on the morning of March 29, 2024, in the town of Juntas, Buenaventura, Colombia. The community gathers during Holy Week to celebrate the Manacillos festival, an ancestral ritual originating in the upper part of the Yurumangui River. Photographer: Nathalia Angarita                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Nathalia Angarita for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Every year during Holy Week leading up to Easter, the community in Juntas, Buenaventura, Colombia, celebrates the Manacillos festival.&lt;/strong&gt; This ancient ritual originated near the Yurumangui River. During the festival, no one is allowed to work in the artisanal gold mines or the agricultural fields in the jungle. The Manacillos festival holds profound spiritual significance, as it reaffirms the residents' African roots and resists colonialism and imposed Catholicism through syncretism, creating a new collective cultural identity.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;📷&lt;strong&gt; See photos&lt;/strong&gt; of how one &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/the-picture-show/2024/10/13/g-s1-15007/how-one-afro-colombian-community-honors-their-ancestry"&gt;Afro-Colombian community honors their ancestry&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-28181" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 7909;         --source-height: 4449;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/7909x4449+0+0/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F61%2Fd7%2F63cb02ff4d0c861ea46861bb93e9%2Fgettyimages-2177675340.jpg" class="img" alt="A SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket with the Europa Clipper spacecraft aboard launches from Launch Complex 39A at NASA's Kennedy Space Center in Cape Canaveral on Monday." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A SpaceX Falcon Heavy rocket with the Europa Clipper spacecraft aboard launches from Launch Complex 39A at NASA's Kennedy Space Center in Cape Canaveral on Monday.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Chandan Khanna/AFP via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Europa Clipper, a spacecraft powered by solar energy, was launched yesterday on a journey of over six years. &lt;/strong&gt;It will study whether one of Jupiter’s moons &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/13/nx-s1-5151863/europa-clipper-jupiter-launch-moon"&gt;can support life&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Three men were awarded this year’s Nobel Prize in Economics for tracing the institutional roots of&lt;/strong&gt; national prosperity in former European colonies. They’ll share the prize, worth about $1.058 million, for their work explaining how the different institutions in those colonies &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/14/nx-s1-5151812/nobel-prize-economics-2024-acemoglu-robinson-johnson-wealth-poverty"&gt;continue to shape economic fortunes today&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Women’s equality activist Lilly Ledbetter died Saturday at 86. &lt;/strong&gt;Her &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/14/nx-s1-5152538/lilly-ledbetter-pay-equity-obituary"&gt;fight for pay equity led to&lt;/a&gt; the passage of the monumental Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Act of 2009.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/859721331/suzanne-nuyen"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
